  count         = 3
  ami           = "ami-123456"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
  tags = {
    Name = "web-${count.index + 1}"
  }
}
```

âœ… Creates `web-1`, `web-2`, `web-3`.

---

### ğŸ§± b) **for_each** Meta-Argument

Used to loop over **maps or sets** with named instances.

```hcl
variable "servers" {
  default = {
    web1 = "t2.micro"
    web2 = "t2.small"
  }
}

resource "aws_instance" "server" {
  for_each      = var.servers
  ami           = "ami-123456"
  instance_type = each.value
  tags = {
    Name = each.key
  }
}
```

âœ… Creates two instances:

* web1 â†’ t2.micro
* web2 â†’ t2.small

---

### ğŸ§± c) **for expressions** (in locals or outputs)

```hcl
locals {
  names = ["app", "db", "cache"]
  upper_names = [for n in local.names : upper(n)]
}

output "upper_names" {
  value = local.upper_names
}
```

âœ… Output:

```
